SIMPLE: travel
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Travel
<hw>Trav"el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Traveled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr> or
<conjf>Travelled</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Traveling</conjf> or <conjf>Travelling</conjf>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[Properly, to labor, and the same word as
<ets>travail</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To labor; to travail.</def>
<mark>[Obsoles.]</mark> <rj><au>Hooker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To go or march on foot; to walk; <as>as, to
<ex>travel</ex> over the city, or through the streets</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To pass by riding, or in any manner, to a distant
place, or to many places; to journey; <as>as, a man <ex>travels</ex> for
his health; he is <ex>traveling</ex> in California.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To pass; to go; to move.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Time <qex>travels</qex> in divers paces with divers persons.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Travel</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Travel
<hw>Trav"el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
journey over; to traverse; <as>as, to <ex>travel</ex> the
continent</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧I <xex>travel</xex> this profound.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To force to journey.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They shall not be <qex>traveled</qex> forth of their own
franchises.</q> <rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Travel</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Travel
<hw>Trav"el</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of traveling,
or journeying from place to place; a journey.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With long <qex>travel</qex> I am stiff and weary.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His <qex>travels</qex> ended at his country seat.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>An account, by a traveler, of
occurrences and observations during a journey; <as>as, a book of
<ex>travels</ex></as>; -- often used as the title of a book; <as>as,
<ex>Travels</ex> in Italy</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>The length of stroke of a
reciprocating piece; <as>as, the <ex>travel</ex> of a slide
valve</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Labor; parturition; travail.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Traveled</ent>⟦br⟧
